ttps://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin />\n    <link\n      href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Chivo:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&family=Inter:ital,opsz,wght@0,14..32,100..900;1,14..32,100..900&family=JetBrains+Mono:ital,wght@0,100..800;1,100..800&display=swap\"\n      rel=\"stylesheet\"\n    />\n    <title>Langflow</title>\n    <script type=\"module\" crossorigin src=\"./assets/index-B-kw73gA.js\"></script>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" crossorigin href=\"./assets/index-BlT0iN5E.css\">\n  </head>\n  <body id=\"body\" class=\"dark\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%\">\n    <noscript>You need to enable JavaScript to run this app.</noscript>\n    <div style=\"width: 100vw; height: 100vh\" id=\"root\"></div>\n  </body>\n</html>","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774443159211}}
{"type":"message","id":"d6b95fc2","parentId":"770d01f5","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:52:50.750Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Need to add LLM profile. Use config reference. Probably need to POST to /api/llm-profiles. Need an API key; unknown. Can't. Might ask user.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The VibeSurf instance is up, but the **browser‑navigate** action can’t run because no LLM profile is configured yet (the error says “No LLM profile available”).  \nTo open the three sites we first need to add a language‑model profile that VibeSurf can use for actions like navigation, summarization, etc.\n\n**Typical steps (you’ll need an API key for a supported provider such as OpenAI, Anthropic, or Claude):**\n\n1. **Pick a provider** – e.g. OpenAI’s `gpt‑4o`, Anthropic’s `claude‑3‑opus`, etc.  \n2. **Get an API key** from the provider’s console.  \n3. **Create the profile** via VibeSurf’s API:\n\n   ```bash\n   curl -X POST http://localhost:9336/api/llm-profiles \\\n        -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n        -d '{\n              \"name\": \"openai-gpt-4o\",\n              \"provider\": \"openai\",\n              \"model\": \"gpt-4o\",\n              \"api_key\": \"YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY\"\n            }'\n   ```\n\n   (Replace the JSON fields with the provider you’re using.)\n\n4. **Verify the profile**:\n\n   ```bash\n   curl http://localhost:9336/api/llm-profiles\n   ```\n\n   You should see the newly added profile in the list.\n\n5. **Now run the navigation commands** (you can open three tabs at once by setting `new_tab: true` for each):\n\n   ```bash\n   curl -X POST http://localhost:9336/api/tool/execute \\\n        -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n        -d '{\n              \"action_name\":\"browser.navigate\",\n              \"parameters\":{\"url\":\"https://www.baidu.com\",\"new_tab\":true}\n            }'\n\n   curl -X POST http://localhost:9336/api/tool/execute \\\n        -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n        -d '{\n              \"action_name\":\"browser.navigate\",\n              \"parameters\":{\"url\":\"https://www.jd.com\",\"new_tab\":true}\n            }'\n\n   curl -X POST http://localhost:9336/api/tool/execute \\\n        -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n        -d '{\n              \"action_name\":\"browser.navigate\",\n              \"parameters\":{\"url\":\"https://www.taobao.com\",\"new_tab\":true}\n            }'\n   ```\n\nIf you prefer not to expose the API key directly, you can also add the profile through VibeSurf’s web UI (`http://localhost:9336/` → *LLM Profiles* section) and then run the navigation calls.\n\n**What you need to do next**\n\n- Provide an API key for a supported LLM, or create the profile via the UI.\n- Once the profile exists, re‑run the navigation calls above and the three sites will open in separate tabs.\n\nLet me know when the LLM profile is added, and I can issue the navigation commands for you."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":17597,"output":720,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18317,"cost":{"input":-17597,"output":-720,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-18317}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774443159217}}
