{"type":"message","id":"26135ebf","parentId":"1670189b","timestamp":"2026-04-08T14:09:30.856Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to share the minimax model. VibeSurf doesn't have minimax listed as a provider. But there's an `openai_compatible` option that accepts a custom base_url. MiniMax has an OpenAI-compatible API endpoint. Let me check if MiniMax has an OpenAI-compatible endpoint.\n\nMiniMax does have an OpenAI-compatible API. The base URL is typically `https://api.minimax.chat/v1` or similar. Let me think about this... Actually, MiniMax's API might be at `https://api.minimax.chat/v1`. The user has minimax configured already for OpenClaw. Let me check if MiniMax has an OpenAI-compatible API.\n \nMiniMax's standard endpoint is `https://api.minimax.chat/v1` with models like `MiniMax-Text-01` and `MiniMax-Text-01-Mini`. Since the user mentioned sharing the system minimax, they're likely referring to the same API key already configured in OpenClaw. MiniMax does support OpenAI-compatible endpoints, so I could use the `openai_compatible` provider type with their base URL to set this up.\n\nThe user probably has an API key configured at `$MINIMAX_API_KEY`, but I should ask for the specific key and base URL rather than trying to access environment variables directly from the VibeSurf container. I'll recommend the `openai_compatible` provider approach and request the necessary credentials to proceed."},{"type":"text","text":"VibeSurf 的 Provider 列表里没有直接的 MiniMax，但有 **openai_compatible** 可以对接 MiniMax 的 OpenAI 兼容接口。\n\n要配置需要两样东西：\n1. **MiniMax 的 API Key**\n2. **MiniMax 的 API Base URL**（MiniMax 提供的是 `https://api.minimax.chat/v1`）\n\n请提供你的 MiniMax API Key，我来配置。或者你在 MiniMax 开放平台上有账号的话，直接给我 Key，我马上把它加进 VibeSurf。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0